  <main class="content">
    <!-- Parent 1  -->
    <section id="types" class="grid">
      <article id="cinematic" class="panel">
        <h3>Cinematic</h3>
        <p>Designed for smooth, stabilized flight with large sensors and slow, graceful camera movement. Cinematic drones are built for film production, weddings, and marketing—where composition, color, and light matter most.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="fpv" class="panel">
        <h3>First-Person-View</h3>
        <p>FPV drones fly through goggles for an immersive experience. They capture thrilling perspectives with fast motion, acrobatic turns, and dynamic storytelling that traditional cameras can’t achieve.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <!-- Parent 2  -->
    <section id="info" class="grid">
      <article id="pros" class="panel">
        <h3>Pros</h3>
        <p><strong>Cinematic drones</strong> deliver stunning, high-resolution footage with precise stabilization, making them ideal for professional video. <strong>FPV drones</strong> provide creative freedom, speed, and angles that bring energy and excitement to every shot.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="cons" class="panel">
        <h3>Cons</h3>
        <p><strong>Cinematic drones</strong> can be bulky, expensive, and require careful setup. <strong>FPV drones</strong> demand more pilot skill, are prone to crashes, and offer shorter flight times.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>

